data:
subjects & related ones are observables
An observable is a concept introduced by rxjs
Its an object that produces and contols a stream of data
operators are an important feature.
Signals vs observables - Looks almost the same to subject
signals are relatively new.
rxjs has operators. Signals doesnt have them.
Observables - pipeline of values emitted over time. Great for managing events & streamed data.
Signals are values in a container. Great for managing application state.
to convert signals to observables,


import { toObservable, toSignal } from '@angular/core/rxjs-interop'

clickCount = signal(0);

constructor() {
toObservable(this.clickCount)
}

// or
clickCount = signal(0);
clickCount$ = toObservable(this.clickCount)

ngOnInit() {
const sub =  this.clickCount$.subscribe({
next: val => console.log(val)
})

this.destroyRef.onDestroy(() => {
sub.unsubscribe()
})
}

Convert observables to signals,
interval$ = interval(1000);

// auto cleans up the subscription too.
intervalSignal = toSignal(this.interval$, {
initialValue: 0,
manualCleanup: true // we dispose the observable manually.
})

